(40, 15, 16, 41, 7, 18, 18, 'without understanding', 'Understanding and Defilement', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of understanding in relation to what defiles a person. The phrase ''without understanding'' appears in both, highlighting the disciples'' lack of insight into Jesus'' teaching about external things not defiling them.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
