(40, 15, 16, 40, 15, 10, 10, 'without understanding', 'Understanding in Jesus'' Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of understanding in Jesus'' teachings. In Matthew 15:10, Jesus calls the multitude to ''Hear, and understand,'' while in Matthew 15:16, He questions the disciples'' lack of understanding.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 16, 42, 9, 45, 45, 'without understanding', 'Understanding and Perception', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding in both passages. In Matthew, Jesus questions the disciples'' lack of understanding, while in Luke, the disciples do not perceive his message, indicating a shared struggle with comprehension.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 16, 23, 28, 9, 10, 'without understanding', 'Understanding and Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding and knowledge in both passages. Jesus questions the disciples'' understanding, paralleling Isaiah''s inquiry about who can comprehend doctrine.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 16, 42, 18, 34, 34, 'without understanding', 'Understanding and Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize a lack of understanding among Jesus'' followers. In Matthew, Jesus questions their understanding, while in Luke, it is stated that the disciples understood none of the things spoken to them.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 17, 42, 6, 45, 45, 'whatsoever entereth in at the mouth', 'Connection of Heart and Mouth', 'This connection highlights the relationship between what enters the body and what comes from the heart. Both passages emphasize that the mouth reveals the true nature of a person, whether through food or speech.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
