(40, 15, 17, 40, 7, 19, 20, NULL, 'Connection of Fruit and Purity', 'This connection highlights the distinction between inner purity and outward actions. Both passages emphasize the consequences of what is produced, whether it be food entering the body or fruit from a tree.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 17, 12, 10, 27, 27, 'cast out into the draught', 'Connection of Purity and Waste', 'This connection highlights the theme of what is considered pure versus impure. In Matthew, the focus is on what enters the body and is expelled, while in 2 Kings, the house of Baal is transformed into a draught house, symbolizing a rejection of idolatry and impurity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 17, 51, 2, 21, 22, 'whatsoever entereth in at the mouth', 'Connection of Dietary Laws', 'This connection highlights the theme of dietary restrictions and their perceived importance. Both passages emphasize the futility of external regulations, as seen in ''whatsoever entereth in at the mouth'' and ''Touch not; taste not; handle not.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 17, 59, 3, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Defilement and Speech', 'This connection highlights the theme of defilement in both passages. Matthew emphasizes that what enters the body does not defile it, while James warns that the tongue can defile the whole body.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 18, 20, 15, 28, 28, 'from the heart', 'Connection of Heart and Speech', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the heart and what is spoken. Matthew highlights that what comes from the heart defiles a person, while Proverbs indicates that the righteous consider their words, contrasting with the wicked who speak evil.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 18, 40, 12, 34, 34, NULL, 'Connection of Heart and Speech', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the heart and speech. They highlight that what comes from the heart defines a person''s words and actions.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 18, 40, 15, 11, 11, NULL, 'Defilement Through Speech', 'Both passages emphasize that it is not what enters the mouth that defiles a man, but rather what comes out of the mouth. This connection highlights the importance of the heart''s intentions as expressed through speech.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 18, 59, 3, 6, 10, 'defile the man', 'Connection of Speech and Heart', 'Both passages emphasize the impact of speech on a person''s moral state. Matthew highlights that what comes from the heart defiles a person, while James elaborates on how the tongue can defile the whole body and produce both blessings and curses.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 18, 20, 10, 32, 32, 'those things which proceed out of the mouth', 'Connection of Speech and Heart', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of speech as a reflection of one''s inner character. Matthew highlights that what comes from the heart defiles a person, while Proverbs contrasts the speech of the righteous and the wicked, indicating that the mouth reveals one''s true nature.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 18, 9, 24, 13, 13, NULL, 'Connection of Wickedness and Heart', 'Both passages emphasize that wickedness originates from within a person''s heart or character. Matthew highlights that defilement comes from the heart, while 1 Samuel notes that wickedness proceeds from the wicked.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 18, 19, 36, 3, 3, 'those things which proceed out of the mouth', 'Connection of Words and Heart', 'Both passages emphasize the moral implications of speech, linking the heart''s condition to the words spoken. Matthew highlights that what comes from the heart defiles, while Psalms describes the mouth''s words as iniquity and deceit.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 19, 41, 7, 21, 23, 'evil thoughts', 'Connection of Evil Thoughts', 'Both passages emphasize that evil thoughts originate from the heart, listing similar sinful actions that defile a person. This connection highlights the consistent biblical theme of internal moral corruption.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 19, 48, 5, 19, 21, 'murders, adulteries, fornications', 'Connection of Evil Actions', 'Both passages emphasize the manifestation of sinful behaviors originating from the heart or flesh. The specific actions listed in Matthew 15:19, such as adultery and murder, are echoed in Galatians 5:19-21, illustrating a shared concern about moral conduct.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 19, 24, 17, 9, 9, 'heart', 'Connection of Heart and Deceit', 'Both passages emphasize the wickedness of the heart. Matthew lists evil thoughts that arise from the heart, while Jeremiah declares the heart as deceitful and wicked.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 19, 56, 3, 2, 6, 'evil thoughts', 'Connection of Evil and Redemption', 'Both passages emphasize the nature of human sinfulness, with Matthew 15:19 listing various evils that arise from the heart, while Titus 3:2-3 describes past behaviors of foolishness and malice. This connection highlights the transformation available through God''s mercy and the Holy Spirit, contrasting the evil thoughts with the renewal offered in Christ.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 19, 59, 1, 13, 15, 'evil thoughts', 'Connection of Sin and Temptation', 'This connection highlights how both passages emphasize the internal origins of sin. Matthew identifies evil thoughts as stemming from the heart, while James explains that temptation arises from one''s own lust.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 19, 20, 4, 23, 23, 'out of the heart', 'Heart and Its Issues', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the heart, with Matthew highlighting the evil that can emerge from it, while Proverbs stresses the need to guard it due to its influence on life. This connection highlights the central role of the heart in moral and spiritual matters.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
